# =====================================================================
# Frontend env overrides (Vite). Copy to frontend/.env.local for local dev,
# or set in the build/deploy environment for prod.
# Read by frontend/src/config/api.js.
# =====================================================================

# The single public origin — the NGINX reverse proxy. NGINX routes
# /api/auth + /api/projects → Express and /api/ai/* → FastAPI internally,
# so the SPA only ever talks to this one URL.
#   • local dev:  http://localhost:80   (the docker-compose `nginx` service)
#   • production: https://api.yourdomain.com
# Local dev: leave VITE_API_URL unset (empty default). The Vite dev proxy
# forwards /api/* to http://localhost:80 (NGINX), so there's zero CORS.
# Production: set to your real domain, e.g. https://api.yourdomain.com
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
